HEADWORD: Paraldehyde
<hw>Par*al"de*hyde</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>para-</ets> + <ets>aldehyde</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
trimer of acetaldehyde (<chform>C6H12O3</chform>), prepared by
polymerization of acetaldehyde with hydrochloric and sulfuric acids. It
has sedative and hypnotic properties.</def> <au>MI11</au>⟦br⟧
